<Base title="Get Your Ham Radio License" description="Resources for getting started in amateur radio — study guides, practice tests, and tips from KH7AL.">
  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.5rem;">

    <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #161b24 0%, #1a2234 100%); border: 1px solid #2a3347; border-left: 3px solid #e8a020; border-radius: 10px; padding: 2rem 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      <div style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.8rem; color: #e8a020; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Amateur Radio Licensing</div>
      <h1 style="font-size: 1.875rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f0f4ff; margin: 0 0 1rem; line-height: 1.2;">Get Your Ham Radio License</h1>
      <p style="color: #7a8ba0; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        Whether you're a seasoned operator looking to upgrade or just starting out, this page is designed to help you get started on your ham journey. Join the ham radio community and explore the exciting world of amateur radio.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">

      <h2>Are you ready?</h2>
      <p>
        If you are reading this then you are at a gateway to adventure, discovery, and connection. Like every great journey, your path to becoming a licensed ham operator begins with curiosity and the courage to try something new. Along the way, you'll encounter challenges, meet mentors, and gain skills that will open doors to global friendships, lifelong learning, and even opportunities to serve your community in times of need. You <em>CAN</em> do it.
      </p>

      <h2>Why Amateur Radio?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Endless Fun</strong> — Talk to fellow radio enthusiasts locally or across the globe. Share stories, participate in contests, or simply enjoy making new connections. The ham radio family consists of people from all walks of life.</li>
        <li><strong>Lifelong Learning</strong> — Amateur radio is a hands-on way to dive into electronics, physics, and communication technology. There's always something new to discover, whether it's building your own equipment, experimenting with antennas, or understanding how signals travel.</li>
        <li><strong>Emergency Communication</strong> — Be a vital link when disaster strikes. Ham radio operators play a crucial role in providing communication when traditional systems fail.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Learn the Basics</strong> — Find resources that explain amateur radio and the licensing process. <a href="https://www.arrl.org/licensing-education-training">Start here at the ARRL</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Study for Your License</strong> — Prepare for the FCC exam with free online resources or local ham radio clubs.</li>
        <li><strong>Join a Community</strong> — Connect with other hams who can help guide you. Your local community likely has a ham radio club willing to help.</li>
        <li><strong>Explore Your Interests</strong> — Whether it's chatting across town or across the globe, amateur radio has endless possibilities.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Free Test Prep and Practice Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://hamstudy.org/"><strong>HamStudy.org</strong></a> — Flash cards, practice exams, and progress tracking</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.qrz.com/hamtest/"><strong>QRZ.com Exam Practice</strong></a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.aa9pw.com/amateur-radio-exam-practice/"><strong>AA9PW Practice Tests</strong></a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.eham.net/exams/"><strong>eHam.net Exams</strong></a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DdzQS10JnHU&list=PL1KAjn5rGhixvvb_jMZFWmbP97-t9Kyxk"><strong>Ham Radio Crash Course</strong></a> — YouTube video series</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Ready to Begin?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.arrl.org/getting-licensed"><strong>ARRL Getting Started Guide</strong></a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.arrl.org/clubs"><strong>Find a Local Ham Radio Club</strong></a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.hamradiolicenseexam.com/"><strong>Online Study Tools for Licensing</strong></a></li>
      </ul>

      <p>If you have further questions feel free to reach out via <a href="https://www.qrz.com/db/KH7AL">QRZ</a> or email <strong>kh7al@arrl.org</strong>.</p>

      <p><em>Embark on your amateur radio adventure today, and unlock a world of opportunities. 73 de KH7AL</em></p>

